"configuration shape"
msgstr ""
"[**Fournisseurs de modèles** → **Aperçu**](../providers/overview.md) — ce "
"que sont les fournisseurs, forme de la configuration"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:7
msgid ""
"[Model Providers → Fallback & routing](../providers/fallback-and-routing.md) "
"— `reliable` and `router` meta-providers"
msgstr ""
"[Proveurs de modèles → Fallback et routage](../providers/fallback-and-"
"routing.md) — méta-proveurs `reliable` et `router`"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:8
msgid ""
"[Model Providers → Catalog](../providers/catalog.md) — every provider's "
"config shape"
msgstr ""
"[Providers de modèles → Catalogue](../providers/catalog.md) — la forme de la "
"configuration de chaque fournisseur"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:10
msgid "When to Use Multi-Model Setup"
msgstr "Quand utiliser une configuration multi-modèle"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:12
msgid "Multi-model configuration is useful for:"
msgstr "La configuration multi-modèles est utile pour :"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:14
msgid ""
"**High reliability**: Automatically fall back to alternative providers when "
"the primary fails"
msgstr ""
"**Haute fiabilité** : Bascule automatiquement vers des fournisseurs "
"alternatifs lorsque le principal échoue"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:15
msgid ""
"**Cost optimization**: Route expensive models through fallback chains for "
"rate-limited scenarios"
msgstr ""
"**Optimisation des coûts** : Acheminer les modèles coûteux via des chaînes "
"de repli pour les scénarios limités en taux"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:16
msgid ""
"**Regional resilience**: Use geographically distributed providers to handle "
"region-specific outages"
msgstr ""
"**Résilience régionale** : Utilisez des fournisseur répartis "
"géographiquement pour gérer les pannes spécifiques à une région"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:17
msgid ""
"**Capability flexibility**: Try different models when one lacks required "
"features (e.g., tool calling, vision)"
msgstr ""
"**Flexibilité des capacités** : Essayez différents modèles lorsque l’un "
"manque de fonctionnalités requises (par exemple, l’appel d’outils, la vision)"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:18
msgid ""
"**Rate limit handling**: Rotate through API keys on `429` (rate limit) "
"responses"
msgstr ""
"**Gestion des limites de taux** : Alterner entre les clés API en cas de "
"réponses `429` (limite de taux)"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:19
msgid ""
"**Development and testing**: Switch between cloud and local models without "
"code changes"
msgstr ""
"**Développement et tests** : Passez des modèles cloud aux modèles locaux "
"sans modifier le code."

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:21
msgid "Core Concepts"
msgstr "Notions fondamentales"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:23
msgid "Fallback Provider Chains"
msgstr "Chaînes de fournisseurs de secours"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:25
msgid ""
"When a provider experiences a transient error (timeout, connection failure, "
"auth issue), ZeroClaw automatically attempts fallback providers in the order "
"specified."
msgstr ""
"Lorsqu'un fournisseur rencontre une erreur transitoire (délai d'attente "
"dépassé, échec de connexion, problème d'authentification), ZeroClaw tente "
"automatiquement les fournisseurs de repli dans l'ordre spécifié."

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:27
msgid ""
"**Example**: If your primary provider is `openai` but it's temporarily "
"unavailable, ZeroClaw can automatically fall back to `anthropic`, then "
"`groq`."
msgstr ""
"**Exemple** : Si votre principal fournisseur est `openai` mais qu'il est "
"temporairement indisponible, ZeroClaw peut automatiquement basculer vers "
"`anthropic`, puis `groq`."

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:29
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[reliability]\n"
"fallback_providers = [\"anthropic\", \"groq\", \"openrouter\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[reliability]\n"
"fallback_providers = [\"anthropic\", \"groq\", \"openrouter\"]\n"
"```"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:34
msgid ""
"When the primary provider recovers, ZeroClaw resumes using it (no sticky "
"failover)."
msgstr ""
"Lorsque le fournisseur principal se rétablit, ZeroClaw reprend son "
"utilisation (pas de basculement persistant)."

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:36
msgid "Model-Level Fallbacks"
msgstr "**Fallbacks au niveau du modèle**"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:38
msgid ""
"Some models may not be available in all regions, or you might want to use a "
"faster model when a heavy model is rate-limited."
msgstr ""
"Certains modèles peuvent ne pas être disponibles dans toutes les régions, ou "
"vous pourriez souhaiter utiliser un modèle plus rapide lorsqu'un modèle "
"lourd est soumis à des limitations de débit."

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:40
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[reliability]\n"
"model_fallbacks = { \"claude-opus-4-7\" = [\"claude-sonnet-4-6\", \"gpt-4o"
"\"] }\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[reliability]\n"
"model_fallbacks = { \"claude-opus-4-7\" = [\"claude-sonnet-4-6\", \"gpt-4o"
"\"] }\n"
"```"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:45
msgid ""
"If `claude-opus-4-7` fails or is unavailable, ZeroClaw tries the fallback "
"models in order while staying within the same provider (unless a provider-"
"level fallback is also configured)."
msgstr ""
"Si `claude-opus-4-7` échoue ou est indisponible, ZeroClaw essaie les modèles "
"de repli dans l'ordre tout en restant dans le même fournisseur (sauf si un "
"repli au niveau du fournisseur est également configuré)."

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:47
msgid "API Key Rotation"
msgstr "Rotation de la clé API"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:49
msgid ""
"For providers that frequently encounter rate limits, you can supply "
"additional API keys that ZeroClaw will rotate through on `429` responses."
msgstr ""
"Pour les fournisseurs qui rencontrent fréquemment des limites de taux, vous "
"pouvez fournir des clés API supplémentaires que ZeroClaw fera varier en cas "
"de réponses `429`."

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:51
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[reliability]\n"
"api_keys = [\"sk-key-2\", \"sk-key-3\", \"sk-key-4\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[rélationnabilité]\n"
"api_keys = [\"sk-key-2\", \"sk-key-3\", \"sk-key-4\"]\n"
"```"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:56
msgid ""
"The primary `api_key` (configured globally or per-channel) is always tried "
"first; these extras are rotated on rate-limit errors."
msgstr ""
"La clé `api_key` principale (configurée globalement ou par canal) est "
"toujours testée en premier ; ces clés supplémentaires sont rotatives en cas "
"d'erreurs de limitation de débit."

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:58
msgid "Provider Retries"
msgstr "Nombre de tentatives du fournisseur"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:60
msgid ""
"Each provider attempt includes configurable retries with exponential backoff "
"before moving to the next fallback."
msgstr ""
"Chaque tentative du fournisseur inclut des tentatives de nouvelle connexion "
"configurables avec un backoff exponentiel avant de passer au prochain "
"secours."

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:68
msgid "Configuration Structure"
msgstr "Structure de configuration"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:70
msgid ""
"All multi-model behavior lives under the `[reliability]` section of `config."
"toml`. See the [Config reference](../reference/config.md) for the full field "
"index and defaults."
msgstr ""
"Tout le comportement relatif aux modèles multiples se trouve dans la section "
"`[reliability]` de `config.toml`. Consultez la [documentation de référence "
"de la configuration](../reference/config.md) pour consulter la liste "
"complète des champs et leurs valeurs par défaut."

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:72
msgid "Example Configurations"
msgstr "Exemples de configurations"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:74
msgid "Basic Fallback Chain"
msgstr "Chaîne de repli de base"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:76
msgid "Set up a simple fallback from your primary provider to a backup:"
msgstr ""
"Configurez une solution de secours simple depuis votre fournisseur principal "
"vers une solution de secours :"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:78
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"default_provider = \"openai\"\n"
"default_model = \"gpt-4o\"\n"
"\n"
"[reliability]\n"
"fallback_providers = [\"anthropic\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"default_provider = \"openai\"\n"
"default_model = \"gpt-4o\"\n"
"\n"
"[reliability]\n"
"fallback_providers = [\"anthropic\"]\n"
"```"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:86
msgid ""
"**Behavior**: If OpenAI times out or returns an error, ZeroClaw will retry "
"twice with exponential backoff, then attempt the same request using "
"Anthropic."
msgstr ""
"**Comportement** : Si OpenAI expire ou renvoie une erreur, ZeroClaw "
"réessaiera deux fois avec une backoff exponentielle, puis tentera d’exécuter "
"la même requête via Anthropic."

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:88
msgid "High-Reliability Multi-Provider Setup"
msgstr "Configuration multi-fournisseuse à haute fiabilité"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:90
msgid "Combine provider fallbacks with model fallbacks and API key rotation:"
msgstr ""
"Combiner les sauts de secours des fournisseurs avec les sauts de secours des "
"modèles et la rotation des clés API :"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:92
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"default_provider = \"openai\"\n"
"default_model = \"gpt-4o\"\n"
"api_key = \"sk-openai-primary\"\n"
"\n"
"[reliability]\n"
"fallback_providers = [\"anthropic\", \"groq\", \"openrouter\"]\n"
"api_keys = [\"sk-openai-backup-1\", \"sk-openai-backup-2\"]\n"
"\n"
"[reliability.model_fallbacks]\n"
"\"gpt-4o\" = [\"gpt-4-turbo\", \"gpt-3.5-turbo\"]\n"
"\"gpt-4-turbo\" = [\"gpt-3.5-turbo\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"default_provider = \"openai\"\n"
"default_model = \"gpt-4o\"\n"
"api_key = \"sk-openai-primary\"\n"
"\n"
"[reliability]\n"
"fallback_providers = [\"anthropic\", \"groq\", \"openrouter\"]\n"
"api_keys = [\"sk-openai-backup-1\", \"sk-openai-backup-2\"]\n"
"\n"
"[reliability.model_fallbacks]\n"
"\"gpt-4o\" = [\"gpt-4-turbo\", \"gpt-3.5-turbo\"]\n"
"\"gpt-4-turbo\" = [\"gpt-3.5-turbo\"]\n"
"```"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:106
msgid "**Behavior**:"
msgstr "**Comportement** :"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:107
msgid "Try OpenAI `gpt-4o` with primary key (2 retries)"
msgstr "Essayer OpenAI `gpt-4o` avec la clé principale (2 tentatives)"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:108
msgid "On rate-limit, rotate to backup API keys"
msgstr "En cas de limitation de taux, basculer vers les clés API de secours."

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:109
msgid ""
"If OpenAI still fails, fall back to Anthropic with same model request "
"(Anthropic will select available equivalent)"
msgstr ""
"Si OpenAI échoue toujours, revenez à Anthropic avec la même requête de "
"modèle (Anthropic sélectionnera l'équivalent disponible)"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:110
msgid "If Anthropic unavailable, try Groq, then OpenRouter"
msgstr "Si Anthropic est indisponible, essayez Groq, puis OpenRouter"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:111
msgid "If model not available, try fallback models in order"
msgstr ""
"Si le modèle n'est pas disponible, essayez les modèles de repli dans l'ordre"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:113
msgid "Local Development with Cloud Fallback"
msgstr "Développement local avec secours via le cloud"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:115
msgid "Use a local Ollama instance as primary, fall back to cloud provider:"
msgstr ""
"Utiliser une instance locale d'Ollama comme principale et faire appel à un "
"fournisseur cloud en tant que solution de secours :"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:117
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"default_provider = \"ollama\"\n"
"default_model = \"llama2:70b\"\n"
"api_url = \"http://localhost:11434\"\n"
"\n"
"[reliability]\n"
"fallback_providers = [\"openrouter\", \"groq\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"default_provider = \"ollama\"\n"
"default_model = \"llama2:70b\"\n"
"api_url = \"http://localhost:11434\"\n"
"\n"
"[reliability]\n"
"fallback_providers = [\"openrouter\", \"groq\"]\n"
"```"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:126
msgid ""
"**Behavior**: If Ollama goes down or times out, automatically use OpenRouter "
"or Groq instead without configuration changes."
msgstr ""
"**Comportement** : Si Ollama est indisponible ou dépasse les délais, "
"basculer automatiquement vers OpenRouter ou Groq sans modification de "
"configuration."

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:128
msgid "Cost Optimization: Heavy Model with Fast Fallback"
msgstr "Optimisation des coûts : modèle lourd avec dégradation rapide"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:130
msgid ""
"Use an expensive reasoning model for complex tasks, but fall back to a "
"faster model:"
msgstr ""
"Utilisez un modèle de raisonnement coûteux pour les tâches complexes, mais "
"revenez à un modèle plus rapide :"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:132
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"default_provider = \"anthropic\"\n"
"default_model = \"claude-opus-4-7\"\n"
"\n"
"[reliability]\n"
"model_fallbacks = { \"claude-opus-4-7\" = [\"claude-sonnet-4-6\"] }\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"default_provider = \"anthropic\"\n"
"default_model = \"claude-opus-4-7\"\n"
"\n"
"[reliability]\n"
"model_fallbacks = { \"claude-opus-4-7\" = [\"claude-sonnet-4-6\"] }\n"
"```"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:140
msgid ""
"**Behavior**: When Opus is rate-limited or slow, automatically use Sonnet "
"(typically 2–3x faster and cheaper)."
msgstr ""
"**Comportement** : Lorsque Opus est rate-limited ou lent, utilisez "
"automatiquement Sonnet (généralement 2 à 3 fois plus rapide et moins cher)."

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:142
msgid "Multi-Region Setup"
msgstr "Configuration multi-régions"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:144
msgid "For organizations with multi-region deployments:"
msgstr "- Pour les organisations avec des déploiements multi-régions :"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:146
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"# Primary US region\n"
"default_provider = \"anthropic\"\n"
"default_model = \"claude-sonnet-4-6\"\n"
"\n"
"[reliability]\n"
"# Fall back to EU region provider if US Anthropic is down\n"
"fallback_providers = [\"bedrock\"]  # AWS Bedrock in multiple regions\n"
"provider_retries = 3\n"
"provider_backoff_ms = 1000\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"# Région principale des États-Unis\n"
"default_provider = \"anthropic\"\n"
"default_model = \"claude-sonnet-4-6\"\n"
"\n"
"[reliability]\n"
"# Utiliser le fournisseur de la région UE en cas de défaillance d'Anthropic "
"aux États-Unis\n"
"fallback_providers = [\"bedrock\"]  # AWS Bedrock sur plusieurs régions\n"
"provider_retries = 3\n"
"provider_backoff_ms = 1000\n"
"```"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:158
msgid "Ensure each fallback provider has credentials in your environment:"
msgstr ""
"- Assurez-vous que chaque fournisseur de secours dispose d'informations "
"d'identification dans votre environnement :"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:161
#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:162
#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:163 src/channels/acp.md:56
#: src/channels/acp.md:57
msgid "\"...\""
msgstr "\"...\""

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:166
msgid "Hot Reload Behavior"
msgstr "Comportement de rechargement à chaud"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:168
msgid ""
"The `[reliability]` section is hot-reloadable. While a channel or gateway is "
"running, updates to `config.toml` take effect on the next inbound message "
"without requiring a restart."
msgstr ""
"La section `[reliability]` est hot-reloadable. Pendant qu’un canal ou une "
"passerelle est en cours d’exécution, les modifications apportées à `config."
"toml` prennent effet lors du prochain message entrant sans nécessiter de "
"redémarrage."

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:170
msgid "Error Handling and Fallback Triggers"
msgstr "Gestion des erreurs et déclencheurs de secours"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:172
msgid "Fallback is triggered by:"
msgstr "Le comportement par défaut est déclenché par :"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:174
msgid "**Timeout**: Provider did not respond within the configured timeout"
msgstr ""
"**Timeout** : Le fournisseur n'a pas répondu dans le délai de timeout "
"configuré"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:175
msgid "**Connection error**: Network/DNS failure"
msgstr "**Erreur de connexion**: Échec réseau/DNS"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:176
msgid ""
"**Auth error**: Invalid credentials (retries only if transient auth service "
"issues detected)"
msgstr ""
"**Erreur d'authentification** : Identifiants invalides (seuls les problèmes "
"transitoires du service d'authentification entraîtent des nouvelles "
"tentatives)"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:177
msgid ""
"**Rate limit (429)**: HTTP 429; triggers API key rotation first, then "
"provider fallback"
msgstr ""
"**Limite de taux (429)** : HTTP 429 ; entraîne d’abord la rotation de la clé "
"API, puis le secours du fournisseur"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:178
msgid "**Service unavailable (503)**: Temporary service issue"
msgstr "**Service indisponible (503)** : problème temporaire de service"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:179
msgid "**Model not found**: Triggers model fallback chain if configured"
msgstr ""
"**Modèle introuvable** : Déclenche la chaîne de repli du modèle si configurée"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:181
msgid "Fallback is **not** triggered by:"
msgstr "Chute non déclenchée par :"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:183
msgid "**Invalid request (400)**: Malformed input; retrying won't help"
msgstr ""
"**Requête invalide (400)** : Entrée malformée ; réessayer ne sera pas utile"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:184
msgid "**Permanent auth failure**: Invalid API key format"
msgstr "**Échec d'authentification permanent** : Format de clé API invalide"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:185
msgid "**Model output errors**: The model responded but returned an error"
msgstr ""
"```text\n"
"**Erreurs de sortie du modèle** : Le modèle a répondu mais a retourné une "
"erreur\n"
"```"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:187
msgid "Debugging Fallback Activity"
msgstr "Activité de secours de débogage"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:189
msgid "Enable runtime traces to debug fallback behavior:"
msgstr ""
"Activer les traces d'exécution pour déboguer le comportement de repli :"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:191
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[observability]\n"
"runtime_trace_mode = \"rolling\"\n"
"runtime_trace_path = \"state/runtime-trace.jsonl\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[observabilité]\n"
"runtime_trace_mode = \"rolling\"\n"
"runtime_trace_path = \"state/runtime-trace.jsonl\"\n"
"```"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:197
msgid "Then query traces:"
msgstr "Puis interroge les traces :"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:200
msgid "# Show all fallback events\n"
msgstr "- Afficher tous les événements de repli\n"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:201
msgid "\"fallback\""
msgstr "\"secours\""

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:202
msgid "# Show provider retry details\n"
msgstr "- Afficher uniquement les détails de retry du fournisseur.\n"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:204
msgid "\"provider\""
msgstr "\"presta"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:205
msgid "# Show rate-limit rotation\n"
msgstr "**Afficher la rotation de la limite de débit**\n"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:207
msgid "\"429\""
msgstr "\"429\""

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:210
msgid "Best Practices"
msgstr "Bonnes pratiques"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:212
msgid ""
"**Order by reliability**: Put most reliable providers first in "
"`fallback_providers`"
msgstr ""
"**Par ordre de fiabilité** : placez les fournisseurs les plus fiables en "
"premier dans `fallback_providers`"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:213
msgid ""
"**Test fallback chains**: Verify fallback behavior before production use"
msgstr ""
"**Vérifiez les chaînes de secours** : Vérifiez le comportement de secours "
"avant une utilisation en production"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:214
msgid ""
"**Monitor API key rotation**: Track rate-limit events to know when rotation "
"is active"
msgstr ""
"**Surveiller la rotation des clés API** : Suivez les événements de "
"limitation de débit pour savoir lorsque la rotation est active"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:215
msgid ""
"**Keep model fallbacks semantically similar**: Don't fall back from a "
"reasoning model to a chat model without intention"
msgstr ""
"**Conserver les modèles de repli sémantiquement semblables** : Ne passez pas "
"d'un modèle de raisonnement à un modèle de chat sans intention"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:216
msgid ""
"**Use environment variables**: Store sensitive API keys in env, not config"
msgstr ""
"**Utiliser les variables d'environnement** : stocker les clés API sensibles "
"dans les variables d'environnement, et non dans les fichiers de "
"configuration."

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:217
msgid ""
"**Document fallback intent**: Add comments in config explaining why each "
"fallback exists"
msgstr ""
"**Documenter la logique de dépannage** : Ajouter des commentaires dans le "
"fichier de configuration pour expliquer la raison d’être de chaque mécanisme "
"de dépannage."

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:218
msgid ""
"**Verify multi-model credentials**: Ensure all fallback providers have valid "
"credentials set"
msgstr ""
"**Vérifier les identifiants multi-modèles** : Assurez-vous que tous les "
"fournisseurs de repli ont des identifiants valides définis"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:220
msgid "Credential Resolution"
msgstr "Résolution des identifiants"

#: src/getting-started/multi-model-setup.md:222
msgid ""
"Each fallback provider resolves credentials independently using the standard "
"resolution order:"
msgstr ""
"Chaque fournisseur de repli résout les identifiants de manière indépendante "
