msgstr "`<PATH>` — Chemin série ou chemin de périphérique"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1275
msgid "`zeroclaw hardware info`"
msgstr "`zeroclaw hardware info`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1277
msgid "Get chip info via USB using probe-rs over ST-Link."
msgstr ""
"Obtenir les informations de la puce via USB en utilisant probe-rs sur ST-"
"Link."

#: src/reference/cli.md:1279
msgid ""
"Queries the target MCU directly through the debug probe without requiring "
"any firmware on the target board."
msgstr ""
"Interroge directement le MCU cible via la sonde de debug sans nécessiter de "
"firmware sur la carte cible."

#: src/reference/cli.md:1281
msgid ""
"Examples: zeroclaw hardware info zeroclaw hardware info --chip STM32F401RETx"
msgstr ""
"Exemples : zeroclaw hardware info zeroclaw hardware info --chip STM32F401RETx"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1285
msgid "**Usage:** `zeroclaw hardware info [OPTIONS]`"
msgstr "**Utilisation :** `zeroclaw hardware info [OPTIONS]`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1289
msgid ""
"`--chip <CHIP>` — Chip name (e.g. STM32F401RETx). Default: STM32F401RETx for "
"Nucleo-F401RE"
msgstr ""
"`--chip <CHIP>` — Nom de la puce (par exemple STM32F401RETx). Par défaut : "
"STM32F401RETx pour Nucleo-F401RE"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1291
msgid "Default value: `STM32F401RETx`"
msgstr "Valeur par défaut : `STM32F401RETx`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1295
msgid "`zeroclaw peripheral`"
msgstr "`zeroclaw périphérique`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1297
msgid "Manage hardware peripherals."
msgstr "Gérer les périphériques matériels."

#: src/reference/cli.md:1299
msgid ""
"Add, list, flash, and configure hardware boards that expose tools to the "
"agent (GPIO, sensors, actuators). Supported boards: nucleo-f401re, rpi-gpio, "
"esp32, arduino-uno."
msgstr ""
"Ajouter, lister, afficher et configurer les cartes matérielles qui exposent "
"des outils à l'agent (GPIO, capteurs, actionneurs). Cartes prises en "
"charge : nucleo-f401re, rpi-gpio, esp32, arduino-uno."

#: src/reference/cli.md:1301
msgid ""
"Examples: zeroclaw peripheral list zeroclaw peripheral add nucleo-f401re /"
"dev/ttyACM0 zeroclaw peripheral add rpi-gpio native zeroclaw peripheral "
"flash --port /dev/cu.usbmodem12345 zeroclaw peripheral flash-nucleo"
msgstr ""
"Exemples :  \n"
"zeroclaw peripheral list  \n"
"zeroclaw peripheral add nucleo-f401re /dev/ttyACM0  \n"
"zeroclaw peripheral add rpi-gpio native  \n"
"zeroclaw peripheral flash --port /dev/cu.usbmodem12345  \n"
"zeroclaw peripheral flash-nucleo"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1308
msgid "**Usage:** `zeroclaw peripheral <COMMAND>`"
msgstr "**Utilisation :** `zeroclaw peripheral <COMMAND>`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1312
msgid "`list` — List configured peripherals"
msgstr "`list` — Liste les périphériques configurés"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1313
msgid "`add` — Add a peripheral (board path, e.g. nucleo-f401re /dev/ttyACM0)"
msgstr ""
"`add` — Ajouter un périphérique (chemin de la carte, par exemple nucleo-"
"f401re /dev/ttyACM0)"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1314
msgid ""
"`flash` — Flash ZeroClaw firmware to Arduino (creates .ino, installs arduino-"
"cli if needed, uploads)"
msgstr ""
"`flash` — Flasher le firmware ZeroClaw sur Arduino (crée un fichier .ino, "
"installe arduino-cli si nécessaire, téléverse)"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1315
msgid ""
"`setup-uno-q` — Setup Arduino Uno Q Bridge app (deploy GPIO bridge for agent "
"control)"
msgstr ""
"`setup-uno-q` — Configurer l'application de pont Arduino Uno Q (déployer le "
"pont GPIO pour le contrôle de l'agent)"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1316
msgid ""
"`flash-nucleo` — Flash ZeroClaw firmware to Nucleo-F401RE (builds + probe-rs "
"run)"
msgstr ""
"`flash-nucleo` — Flasher le firmware ZeroClaw sur un Nucleo-F401RE "
"(compilation + exécution avec probe-rs)"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1320
msgid "`zeroclaw peripheral list`"
msgstr "`liste des périphériques zeroclaw`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1322
msgid "List configured peripherals"
msgstr "Liste des périphériques configurés"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1324
msgid "**Usage:** `zeroclaw peripheral list`"
msgstr "**Utilisation :** `zeroclaw peripheral list`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1328
msgid "`zeroclaw peripheral add`"
msgstr "`zeroclaw peripheral add`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1330
msgid "Add a peripheral by board type and transport path."
msgstr "Ajouter une périphérique par type de carte et chemin de transport."

#: src/reference/cli.md:1332
msgid ""
"Registers a hardware board so the agent can use its tools (GPIO, sensors, "
"actuators). Use 'native' as path for local GPIO on single-board computers "
"like Raspberry Pi."
msgstr ""
"Enregistre une carte matérielle afin que l'agent puisse utiliser ses outils "
"(GPIO, capteurs, actionneurs). Utilisez 'native' comme chemin pour le GPIO "
"local sur les ordinateurs monocartes comme le Raspberry Pi."

#: src/reference/cli.md:1334
msgid "Supported boards: nucleo-f401re, rpi-gpio, esp32, arduino-uno."
msgstr "Cartes prises en charge : nucleo-f401re, rpi-gpio, esp32, arduino-uno."

#: src/reference/cli.md:1336
msgid ""
"Examples: zeroclaw peripheral add nucleo-f401re /dev/ttyACM0 zeroclaw "
"peripheral add rpi-gpio native zeroclaw peripheral add esp32 /dev/ttyUSB0"
msgstr ""
"Exemples : zeroclaw peripheral add nucleo-f401re /dev/ttyACM0 zeroclaw "
"peripheral add rpi-gpio native zeroclaw peripheral add esp32 /dev/ttyUSB0"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1341
msgid "**Usage:** `zeroclaw peripheral add <BOARD> <PATH>`"
msgstr "**Utilisation :** `zeroclaw peripheral add <BOARD> <PATH>`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1345
msgid "`<BOARD>` — Board type (nucleo-f401re, rpi-gpio, esp32)"
msgstr "`<BOARD>` — Type de carte (nucleo-f401re, rpi-gpio, esp32)"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1346
msgid ""
"`<PATH>` — Path for serial transport (/dev/ttyACM0) or \"native\" for local "
"GPIO"
msgstr ""
"`<PATH>` — Chemin pour le transport série (/dev/ttyACM0) ou « native » pour "
"GPIO local"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1350
msgid "`zeroclaw peripheral flash`"
msgstr "`zeroclaw peripheral flash`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1352
msgid "Flash ZeroClaw firmware to an Arduino board."
msgstr "Flasher le firmware ZeroClaw sur une carte Arduino."

#: src/reference/cli.md:1354
msgid ""
"Generates the .ino sketch, installs arduino-cli if it is not already "
"available, compiles, and uploads the firmware."
msgstr ""
"Génère le croquis .ino, installe arduino-cli s'il n'est pas déjà disponible, "
"compile et télécharge le firmware."

#: src/reference/cli.md:1356
msgid ""
"Examples: zeroclaw peripheral flash zeroclaw peripheral flash --port /dev/cu."
"usbmodem12345 zeroclaw peripheral flash -p COM3"
msgstr ""
"Exemples : flash de la périphérie zeroclaw flash de la périphérie zeroclaw --"
"port /dev/cu.usbmodem12345 flash de la périphérie zeroclaw -p COM3"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1361
msgid "**Usage:** `zeroclaw peripheral flash [OPTIONS]`"
msgstr "**Utilisation :** `zeroclaw peripheral flash [OPTIONS]`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1365
msgid ""
"`-p`, `--port <PORT>` — Serial port (e.g. /dev/cu.usbmodem12345). If "
"omitted, uses first arduino-uno from config"
msgstr ""
"`-p`, `--port <PORT>` — Port série (par exemple /dev/cu.usbmodem12345). Si "
"omis, utilise le premier arduino-uno de la configuration."

#: src/reference/cli.md:1369
msgid "`zeroclaw peripheral setup-uno-q`"
msgstr "`zeroclaw périphérique configuration-uno-q`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1371
msgid "Setup Arduino Uno Q Bridge app (deploy GPIO bridge for agent control)"
msgstr ""
"Configurer l'application Arduino Uno Q Bridge (déployer le pont GPIO pour le "
"contrôle de l'agent)"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1373
msgid "**Usage:** `zeroclaw peripheral setup-uno-q [OPTIONS]`"
msgstr "**Utilisation :** `zeroclaw peripheral setup-uno-q [OPTIONS]`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:1377
msgid ""
"`--host <HOST>` — Uno Q IP (e.g. 192.168.0.48). If omitted, assumes running "
"ON the Uno Q"
msgstr ""
"`--host <HOST>` — IP de Uno Q (par exemple 192.168.0.48). Si omis, suppose "
"que le programme s'exécute SUR Uno Q."

#: src/reference/cli.md:1381 src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:38
#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:116
