#: src/providers/configuration.md:1
msgid "Provider Configuration"
msgstr "Configuration du fournisseur"

#: src/providers/configuration.md:3
msgid ""
"Every model provider is declared under `[providers.models.<name>]` in `~/."
"zeroclaw/config.toml`. The `<name>` is your own alias — it's how you "
"reference the provider elsewhere in config (`default_model = \"claude\"`, "
"`fallback_providers = [\"claude\", \"local\"]`, etc.)."
msgstr ""
"Chaque fournisseur de modèle est déclaré sous `[providers.models.<nom>]` "
"dans `~/.zeroclaw/config.toml`. Le `<nom>` est votre propre alias — c’est "
"ainsi que vous référencez le fournisseur ailleurs dans la configuration "
"(`default_model = \"claude\"`, `fallback_providers = [\"claude\", \"local"
"\"]`, etc.)."

#: src/providers/configuration.md:5
msgid "Minimum shape"
msgstr "Forme minimale"

#: src/providers/configuration.md:7
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[providers.models.<name>]\n"
"kind = \"<provider-kind>\"   # required — selects the implementation\n"
"model = \"<model-id>\"       # required — passed to the provider\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[providers.models.<name>]\n"
"kind = \"<provider-kind>\"   # requis — sélectionne l'implémentation\n"
"model = \"<model-id>\"       # requis — transmis au fournisseur\n"
"```"

#: src/providers/configuration.md:13
msgid "Almost every provider also takes:"
msgstr "Presque tous les fournisseurs acceptent également :"

#: src/providers/configuration.md:15
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"api_key = \"...\"            # or an env-var placeholder\n"
"base_url = \"https://...\"   # for OpenAI-compatible or self-hosted "
"endpoints\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"api_key = \"...\"            # ou un espace réservé de variable "
"d'environnement\n"
"base_url = \"https://...\"   # pour les points de terminaison compatibles "
"OpenAI ou auto-hébergés\n"
"```"

