#: src/channels/social.md:1
msgid "Social Channels"
msgstr "Canaux sociaux"

#: src/channels/social.md:3
msgid ""
"Broadcast / social-feed integrations. These differ from chat channels in two "
"ways: messages are typically public, and the agent often acts as a poster "
"rather than a bidirectional responder."
msgstr ""
"Intégrations de diffusion / flux sociaux. Ces dernières diffèrent des canaux "
"de chat en deux points : les messages sont généralement publics et l’agent "
"agit souvent comme un diffuseur plutôt que comme un répondant bidirectionnel."

#: src/channels/social.md:5
msgid "Bluesky (AT Protocol)"
msgstr "Bluesky (protocole AT)"

#: src/channels/social.md:7
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.bluesky]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"handle = \"you.bsky.social\"\n"
"app_password = \"xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx\"      # create at bsky.app/settings/"
"app-passwords\n"
"allowed_mentions = [\"@trustedfriend.bsky.social\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.bluesky]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"handle = \"you.bsky.social\"\n"
"app_password = \"xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx\"      # créer à l'adresse bsky.app/"
"settings/app-passwords\n"
"allowed_mentions = [\"@trustedfriend.bsky.social\"]\n"
"```"

#: src/channels/social.md:15
msgid ""
"**Auth:** Bluesky app-password (not your real password). Create one in "
"settings."
msgstr ""
"**Auth :** mot de passe d'application Bluesky (pas votre vrai mot de passe). "
"Créez-en un dans les paramètres."

#: src/channels/social.md:16
msgid ""
"**Inbound:** mentions and direct messages trigger the agent. Scope with "
"`allowed_mentions`."
msgstr ""
"**Entrant :** les mentions et les messages directs déclenchent l'agent. "
"Limitez la portée avec `allowed_mentions`."

#: src/channels/social.md:17
msgid "**Outbound:** 300-character posts; longer responses auto-thread."
msgstr ""
"**Sortant :** publications de 300 caractères ; les réponses plus longues "
"sont automatiquement divisées en plusieurs fils."

#: src/channels/social.md:18
msgid "**Protocol:** AT Protocol via `atrium-api` crate."
msgstr "**Protocole :** Protocole AT via le crate `atrium-api`."

#: src/channels/social.md:22
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.nostr]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"private_key_hex = \"...\"                   # nsec in hex\n"
"relays = [\n"
"    \"wss://relay.damus.io\",\n"
"    \"wss://nos.lol\",\n"
"    \"wss://relay.primal.net\",\n"
"]\n"
"allowed_pubkeys = [\"npub1...\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.nostr]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"private_key_hex = \"...\"                   # nsec en hexadécimal\n"
"relays = [\n"
"    \"wss://relay.damus.io\",\n"
"    \"wss://nos.lol\",\n"
"    \"wss://relay.primal.net\",\n"
"]\n"
"allowed_pubkeys = [\"npub1...\"]\n"
"```"

#: src/channels/social.md:34
msgid ""
"**Auth:** raw private key. Store in the encrypted secrets backend — never in "
"a checked-in config."
msgstr ""
"**Auth :** clé privée brute. À stocker dans le backend de secrets chiffrés — "
"jamais dans une configuration versionnée."

#: src/channels/social.md:35
msgid ""
"**Inbound:** kind-1 (text), kind-4 (DM, NIP-04), and kind-1059 (gift-wrap, "
"NIP-17)."
msgstr ""
"**Entrant :** kind-1 (texte), kind-4 (DM, NIP-04) et kind-1059 (cadeau-"
"emballé, NIP-17)."

#: src/channels/social.md:36
msgid "**Outbound:** same kinds. Zap handling is experimental."
msgstr "**Sortant :** mêmes types. La gestion des Zap est expérimentale."

#: src/channels/social.md:37
msgid ""
"**Relays:** the agent connects to all listed relays; use 3–5 for reliability."
msgstr ""
"**Relais :** l'agent se connecte à tous les relais listés ; utilisez 3 à 5 "
"pour la fiabilité."

#: src/channels/social.md:41
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.twitter]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"api_key = \"...\"\n"
"api_secret = \"...\"\n"
"access_token = \"...\"\n"
"access_secret = \"...\"\n"
"bearer_token = \"...\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.twitter]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"api_key = \"...\"\n"
"api_secret = \"...\"\n"
"access_token = \"...\"\n"
"access_secret = \"...\"\n"
"bearer_token = \"...\"\n"
"```"

#: src/channels/social.md:51
msgid ""
"**Auth:** OAuth 1.0a app credentials. Requires Twitter Developer Portal "
"access — paid tier for full API v2 access."
msgstr ""
"**Auth :** Identifiants d'application OAuth 1.0a. Nécessite un accès au "
"Twitter Developer Portal — abonnement payant pour un accès complet à l'API "
"v2."

#: src/channels/social.md:52
msgid "**Inbound:** mentions via the Filtered Stream endpoint."
msgstr "**Entrant :** mentions via le point de terminaison du flux filtré."

#: src/channels/social.md:53
msgid "**Outbound:** posts, replies, threads."
msgstr "**Sortant :** publications, réponses, fils de discussion."

#: src/channels/social.md:54
msgid ""
"**Caveat:** the free tier is rate-limited to the point of near-uselessness. "
"Budget accordingly."
msgstr ""
"**Avertissement :** le plan gratuit est soumis à des limites de débit qui le "
"rendent presque inutilisable. Prévoyez votre budget en conséquence."

#: src/channels/social.md:58
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.reddit]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"client_id = \"...\"\n"
"client_secret = \"...\"\n"
"username = \"...\"\n"
"password = \"...\"                          # or use refresh_token\n"
"user_agent = \"zeroclaw-agent/0.1 by your-username\"\n"
"subreddits = [\"rust\", \"commandline\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.reddit]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"client_id = \"...\"\n"
"client_secret = \"...\"\n"
"username = \"...\"\n"
"password = \"...\"                          # ou utilisez refresh_token\n"
"user_agent = \"zeroclaw-agent/0.1 by your-username\"\n"
"subreddits = [\"rust\", \"commandline\"]\n"
"```"

#: src/channels/social.md:69
msgid ""
"**Auth:** OAuth 2.0 password flow or refresh token. Password flow requires a "
"script-type app."
msgstr ""
"**Auth :** flux OAuth 2.0 avec mot de passe ou jeton d'actualisation. Le "
"flux avec mot de passe nécessite une application de type script."

#: src/channels/social.md:70
msgid ""
"**Inbound:** new posts and comments in the configured subreddits, plus "
"replies to the agent's own posts."
msgstr ""
"**Entrant :** nouveaux messages et commentaires dans les subreddits "
"configurés, ainsi que les réponses aux propres messages de l'agent."

#: src/channels/social.md:71
msgid "**Outbound:** posts, comments, private messages."
msgstr "**Sortant :** publications, commentaires, messages privés."

#: src/channels/social.md:72
msgid ""
"**User-agent convention:** Reddit's API requires a descriptive user-agent "
"string. Non-compliance → rate limits."
msgstr ""
"**Convention de l'agent utilisateur :** L'API de Reddit exige une chaîne "
"d'agent utilisateur descriptive. Le non-respect entraîne des limites de taux."

#: src/channels/social.md:76
msgid "Operating social channels safely"
msgstr "Gérer les canaux sociaux en toute sécurité"

#: src/channels/social.md:78
msgid ""
"Bots on public social networks attract adversarial input. Two precautions:"
msgstr ""
"Les bots sur les réseaux sociaux publics attirent des entrées malveillantes. "
"Deux précautions :"

#: src/channels/social.md:80
msgid ""
"**Restrict who the agent will respond to.** Use `allowed_mentions` / "
"`allowed_pubkeys` / `allowed_users` to whitelist. The default empty-list "
"behaviour varies per channel — check each."
msgstr ""
"**Restreindre les destinataires auxquels l'agent peut répondre.** Utilisez "
"`allowed_mentions` / `allowed_pubkeys` / `allowed_users` pour définir une "
"liste blanche. Le comportement par défaut (liste vide) varie selon le type "
"de canal — vérifiez chaque cas."

#: src/channels/social.md:81
msgid ""
"**Keep autonomy level at `Supervised` or lower.** A public-facing agent in "
"`Full` autonomy is effectively a public shell. If you want to run public-"
"facing, disable shell tools for that channel:"
msgstr ""
"**Maintenez le niveau d'autonomie à `Supervised` ou inférieur.** Un agent "
"accessible au public en autonomie `Full` est essentiellement un shell "
"public. Si vous souhaitez exécuter un agent accessible au public, désactivez "
"les outils de shell pour ce canal :"

#: src/channels/social.md:83
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.bluesky]\n"
"tools_allow = [\"http\", \"web_search\"]      # whitelist — no shell, no "
"file_write\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.bluesky]\n"
"tools_allow = [\"http\", \"web_search\"]      # liste blanche — pas de "
"shell, pas de file_write\n"
"```"

#: src/channels/social.md:88
msgid "Rate limits and backoff"
msgstr "Limites de taux et mécanisme de backoff"

#: src/channels/social.md:90
msgid ""
"All social channels are subject to aggressive rate limits. ZeroClaw's "
"outbound queue uses exponential backoff on 429 responses. If you hit "
"persistent rate-limiting, lower `draft_update_interval_ms` and check whether "
"you're accidentally editing messages (Bluesky does not support edits; others "
"have per-operation limits)."
msgstr ""
"Tous les canaux sociaux sont soumis à des limites de débit agressives. La "
"file de sortie de ZeroClaw utilise un backoff exponentiel en cas de réponses "
"429. Si vous rencontrez des limitations de débit persistantes, réduisez la "
"valeur de `draft_update_interval_ms` et vérifiez si vous modifiez "
"accidentellement des messages (Bluesky ne prend pas en charge les "
"modifications ; d'autres plateformes ont des limites par opération)."

#: src/channels/email.md:3
msgid ""
"Two email channels depending on how you want inbound messages delivered."
msgstr ""
"Deux canaux de messagerie électronique en fonction de la manière dont vous "
"souhaitez recevoir les messages entrants."

#: src/channels/email.md:5
msgid "IMAP + SMTP (`email_channel`)"
msgstr "IMAP + SMTP (`email_channel`)"

#: src/channels/email.md:7
msgid ""
"The general-purpose email channel. Polls IMAP for new messages, sends via "
"SMTP. Works with Gmail, Outlook, Fastmail, self-hosted Postfix, and anything "
"else that speaks IMAP/SMTP."
msgstr ""
"Le canal de messagerie polyvalent. Interroge IMAP pour les nouveaux messages "
"et envoie via SMTP. Fonctionne avec Gmail, Outlook, Fastmail, Postfix auto-"
"hébergé et tout autre service compatible IMAP/SMTP."

#: src/channels/email.md:9
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.email]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"\n"
"[channels.email.imap]\n"
"host = \"imap.example.com\"\n"
"port = 993\n"
"username = \"you@example.com\"\n"
"password = \"...\"                 # or app-password for Gmail/iCloud\n"
"mailbox = \"INBOX\"\n"
"poll_interval_secs = 60\n"
"\n"
"[channels.email.smtp]\n"
"host = \"smtp.example.com\"\n"
"port = 587\n"
"username = \"you@example.com\"\n"
"password = \"...\"\n"
"\n"
"[channels.email.filter]\n"
"allowed_senders = [\"boss@example.com\", \"alerts@example.com\"]\n"
"subject_prefix = \"[agent]\"       # only respond to subjects starting with "
"this\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.email]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"\n"
"[channels.email.imap]\n"
"host = \"imap.example.com\"\n"
"port = 993\n"
"username = \"you@example.com\"\n"
"password = \"...\"                 # ou mot de passe d'application pour "
"Gmail/iCloud\n"
"mailbox = \"INBOX\"\n"
"poll_interval_secs = 60\n"
"\n"
"[channels.email.smtp]\n"
"host = \"smtp.example.com\"\n"
"port = 587\n"
"username = \"you@example.com\"\n"
"password = \"...\"\n"
"\n"
"[channels.email.filter]\n"
"allowed_senders = [\"boss@example.com\", \"alerts@example.com\"]\n"
"subject_prefix = \"[agent]\"       # répondre uniquement aux objets "
"commençant par ce préfixe\n"
"```"

#: src/channels/email.md:32
msgid "Gmail gotchas"
msgstr "Pièges courants avec Gmail"

#: src/channels/email.md:34
msgid ""
"**App passwords required** if 2FA is on. Regular account password is "
"rejected."
msgstr ""
"**Les mots de passe d'application sont requis** si l'authentification à deux "
"facteurs (2FA) est activée. Le mot de passe du compte régulier est refusé."

#: src/channels/email.md:35
msgid "**\"Less secure app access\" is gone** — app password is the only path."
msgstr ""
"**« Accès des applications moins sécurisées » a disparu** — le mot de passe "
"d'application est le seul moyen."

#: src/channels/email.md:36
msgid ""
"Consider the Gmail Push channel below for real-time delivery instead of "
"polling."
msgstr ""
"Considérez le canal de poussée Gmail ci-dessous pour une livraison en temps "
"réel au lieu d’un sondage."

#: src/channels/email.md:38
msgid "Outlook / Office 365"
msgstr "Outlook / Office 365"

#: src/channels/email.md:40
msgid "OAuth 2.0 is recommended over password auth:"
msgstr ""
"OAuth 2.0 est recommandé par rapport à l'authentification par mot de passe :"

#: src/channels/email.md:42
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.email.imap]\n"
"host = \"outlook.office365.com\"\n"
"port = 993\n"
"username = \"you@example.com\"\n"
"oauth_token = \"...\"              # managed via `zeroclaw channel auth "
"email`\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.email.imap]\n"
"host = \"outlook.office365.com\"\n"
"port = 993\n"
"username = \"you@example.com\"\n"
"oauth_token = \"...\"              # géré via `zeroclaw channel auth email`\n"
"```"

#: src/channels/email.md:50
msgid "Gmail Push (`gmail_push`)"
msgstr "Gmail Push (`gmail_push`)"

#: src/channels/email.md:52
msgid "Real-time delivery via Google Cloud Pub/Sub — no polling."
msgstr "Livraison en temps réel via Google Cloud Pub/Sub — sans interrogation."

#: src/channels/email.md:54
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.gmail_push]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"account = \"you@gmail.com\"\n"
"client_secret_json = \"~/.zeroclaw/gmail-client-secret.json\"\n"
"pubsub_topic = \"projects/my-project/topics/gmail-inbox\"\n"
"pubsub_subscription = \"projects/my-project/subscriptions/zeroclaw-sub\"\n"
"allowed_senders = [\"boss@example.com\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.gmail_push]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"account = \"you@gmail.com\"\n"
"client_secret_json = \"~/.zeroclaw/gmail-client-secret.json\"\n"
"pubsub_topic = \"projects/my-project/topics/gmail-inbox\"\n"
"pubsub_subscription = \"projects/my-project/subscriptions/zeroclaw-sub\"\n"
"allowed_senders = [\"boss@example.com\"]\n"
"```"

#: src/channels/email.md:66
msgid "Create a Google Cloud project, enable Gmail API and Pub/Sub API"
msgstr "Créez un projet Google Cloud, activez l'API Gmail et l'API Pub/Sub."

#: src/channels/email.md:67
msgid "Create a Pub/Sub topic the Gmail service can publish to"
msgstr "Créer un sujet Pub/Sub auquel le service Gmail peut publier"

#: src/channels/email.md:68
msgid "Create a pull subscription on that topic for ZeroClaw"
msgstr "Créez une souscription pull sur ce sujet pour ZeroClaw"

#: src/channels/email.md:69
msgid "Create OAuth client credentials (desktop app type), download JSON"
msgstr ""
"Créer des identifiants de client OAuth (type application de bureau), "
"télécharger le fichier JSON"

#: src/channels/email.md:70
msgid ""
"On first run, `zeroclaw channel auth gmail-push` opens a browser for the "
"OAuth consent"
msgstr ""
"Lors de la première exécution, `zeroclaw channel auth gmail-push` ouvre un "
"navigateur pour le consentement OAuth."

#: src/channels/email.md:71
msgid "The agent watches the subscription for new-mail notifications"
msgstr ""
"L'agent surveille l'abonnement pour les notifications de nouveaux messages."

#: src/channels/email.md:73
msgid ""
"Outbound sends still go via SMTP — configure an `smtp` block in this channel "
"the same way as the IMAP+SMTP channel."
msgstr ""
"Les envois sortants continuent de passer par SMTP — configurez un bloc "
"`smtp` dans ce canal de la même manière que pour le canal IMAP+SMTP."

#: src/channels/email.md:77
msgid "Reply threading"
msgstr "Réponses en fil de discussion"

#: src/channels/email.md:79
msgid ""
"Both email channels thread replies using `In-Reply-To` and `References` "
"headers so conversations stay grouped in whatever client the sender uses."
msgstr ""
"Les deux canaux de messagerie électronique regroupent les réponses en "
"utilisant les en-têtes `In-Reply-To` et `References`, afin que les "
"conversations restent groupées dans le client que l'expéditeur utilise."

#: src/channels/email.md:81
msgid "Attachment handling"
msgstr "Gestion des pièces jointes"

#: src/channels/email.md:83
msgid ""
"Inbound attachments are stored under `<workspace>/attachments/<conversation>/"
"`. The agent gets file paths in its context and can read them via the "
"`file_read` tool."
msgstr ""
"Les pièces jointes entrantes sont stockées sous `<workspace>/attachments/"
"<conversation>/`. L'agent reçoit les chemins des fichiers dans son contexte "
"et peut les lire via l'outil `file_read`."

#: src/channels/email.md:85
msgid ""
"Outbound attachments are not supported yet — the agent replies with links to "
"files in the workspace, and the user downloads via whatever tunnel the "
"workspace is exposed through."
msgstr ""
"Les pièces jointes sortantes ne sont pas encore prises en charge — l’agent "
"répond avec des liens vers des fichiers dans l’espace de travail, et "
"l’utilisateur les télécharge via le tunnel par lequel l’espace de travail "
"est exposé."

#: src/channels/email.md:87
msgid "Rate and volume limits"
msgstr "Limites de taux et de volume"

#: src/channels/email.md:89
msgid "Email isn't optimised for conversational latency. Expect:"
msgstr ""
"L'e-mail n'est pas optimisé pour la latence conversationnelle. Attendez-vous "
"à :"

#: src/channels/email.md:91
msgid ""
"IMAP poll latency: `poll_interval_secs` (default 60 s). Lower at the cost of "
"server load; some providers rate-limit aggressive polling."
msgstr ""
"Latence de l'interrogation IMAP : `poll_interval_secs` (par défaut 60 s). "
"Réduisez cette valeur au détriment de la charge du serveur ; certains "
"fournisseurs limitent le nombre d'interrogations agressives."

#: src/channels/email.md:92
msgid ""
"SMTP send: subject to your provider's daily-send quota (Gmail: 500/day for "
"free accounts, 2000/day for Workspace)."
msgstr ""
"Envoi SMTP : soumis au quota quotidien d'envois de votre fournisseur "
"(Gmail : 500/jour pour les comptes gratuits, 2000/jour pour Workspace)."

#: src/channels/email.md:94 src/hardware/index.md:67
msgid "Safety"
msgstr "Sécurité"

#: src/channels/email.md:96
msgid ""
"Email has no auth at the protocol level beyond SMTP's envelope — anyone can "
"claim to be anyone. Always configure `allowed_senders` (strict list of "
"addresses) or `subject_prefix` (shared secret in the subject line) before "
"exposing the agent to an inbox that receives public mail."
msgstr ""
"L’email ne dispose d’aucune authentification au niveau du protocole au-delà "
"de l’enveloppe SMTP — n’importe qui peut prétendre être n’importe qui. "
"Configurez toujours `allowed_senders` (liste stricte d’adresses) ou "
"`subject_prefix` (secret partagé dans l’objet du message) avant d’exposer "
"l’agent à une boîte de réception qui reçoit des courriers publics."

#: src/channels/voice.md:1
msgid "Voice & Telephony"
msgstr "Voix et Téléphonie"

#: src/channels/voice.md:3
msgid ""
"Real-time voice input and output. Four channels cover the matrix: inbound "
"calls, outbound speech synthesis, local microphone wake, and SIP-grade real-"
"time conversation."
msgstr ""
"Entrée et sortie vocales en temps réel. Quatre canaux couvrent la matrice : "
"appels entrants, synthèse vocale sortante, éveil par microphone local et "
"conversation en temps réel de qualité SIP."

#: src/channels/voice.md:5
msgid "ClawdTalk (real-time SIP)"
msgstr "ClawdTalk (SIP en temps réel)"

#: src/channels/voice.md:7
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.clawdtalk]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"telnyx_api_key = \"...\"\n"
"connection_id = \"...\"              # Telnyx SIP connection\n"
"model_provider = \"voice-brain\"     # references [providers.models.voice-"
"brain]\n"
"voice = \"Polly.Joanna-Neural\"      # Telnyx voice ID\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.clawdtalk]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"telnyx_api_key = \"...\"\n"
"connection_id = \"...\"              # Connexion SIP Telnyx\n"
"model_provider = \"voice-brain\"     # fait référence à [providers.models."
"voice-brain]\n"
"voice = \"Polly.Joanna-Neural\"      # ID de voix Telnyx\n"
"```"

#: src/channels/voice.md:16
msgid ""
"Full-duplex SIP voice powered by Telnyx. The agent talks over a real phone "
"call — inbound or outbound. Supports barge-in, mid-turn tool use, and "
"regional number provisioning."
msgstr ""
"Voix SIP full-duplex propulsée par Telnyx. L’agent parle lors d’un appel "
"téléphonique réel — entrant ou sortant. Prend en charge l’interruption en "
"cours de parole, l’utilisation d’outils en milieu de tour de parole et la "
"provisionnement de numéros régionaux."

#: src/channels/voice.md:18
msgid ""
"**Pair with:** a `telnyx` provider for the brain (`crates/zeroclaw-providers/"
"src/telnyx.rs`) and ensure your Telnyx account has a SIP connection with the "
"correct webhook URL pointed at the ZeroClaw gateway."
msgstr ""
"**Associer avec :** un fournisseur `telnyx` pour le cerveau (`crates/"
"zeroclaw-providers/src/telnyx.rs`) et assurez-vous que votre compte Telnyx "
"dispose d’une connexion SIP avec l’URL de webhook correcte pointant vers la "
"passerelle ZeroClaw."

#: src/channels/voice.md:20
msgid "Voice Call (Twilio / Telnyx / Plivo)"
msgstr "Appel vocal (Twilio / Telnyx / Plivo)"

#: src/channels/voice.md:22
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.voice_call]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"carrier = \"twilio\"                 # or \"telnyx\", \"plivo\"\n"
"account_sid = \"...\"\n"
"auth_token = \"...\"\n"
"from_number = \"+14155550123\"\n"
"stt_provider = \"whisper\"\n"
"tts_provider = \"elevenlabs\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.voice_call]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"carrier = \"twilio\"                 # ou \"telnyx\", \"plivo\"\n"
"account_sid = \"...\"\n"
"auth_token = \"...\"\n"
"from_number = \"+14155550123\"\n"
"stt_provider = \"whisper\"\n"
"tts_provider = \"elevenlabs\"\n"
"```"

#: src/channels/voice.md:33
msgid ""
"Traditional carrier voice — the agent picks up, transcribes with STT, "
"replies with TTS. Higher latency than ClawdTalk but works with any regular "
"phone number and doesn't require SIP trunk provisioning."
msgstr ""
"Voix traditionnelle de l'opérateur — l'agent décroche, transcrit avec STT, "
"répond avec TTS. Latence plus élevée que ClawdTalk mais fonctionne avec "
"n'importe quel numéro de téléphone standard et ne nécessite pas de "
"provisionnement de tronc SIP."

#: src/channels/voice.md:35
msgid "Voice Wake (local wake-word)"
msgstr "Réveil vocal (mot d'éveil local)"

#: src/channels/voice.md:37
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.voice_wake]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"wake_phrase = \"hey claw\"\n"
"engine = \"porcupine\"               # or \"openwakeword\"\n"
"model_path = \"~/.zeroclaw/wake/hey-claw.ppn\"\n"
"audio_device = \"default\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.voice_wake]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"wake_phrase = \"hey claw\"\n"
"engine = \"porcupine\"               # ou \"openwakeword\"\n"
"model_path = \"~/.zeroclaw/wake/hey-claw.ppn\"\n"
"audio_device = \"default\"\n"
"```"

#: src/channels/voice.md:46
msgid ""
"Runs locally, listens on the mic, triggers agent interaction when it hears "
"the wake phrase. Useful for:"
msgstr ""
"S'exécute localement, écoute via le microphone et déclenche l'interaction "
"avec l'agent lorsqu'il entend le mot d'éveil. Utile pour :"

#: src/channels/voice.md:48
msgid "Physical voice assistants on SBCs"
msgstr "Assistants vocaux physiques sur les SBC"

#: src/channels/voice.md:49
msgid "Desktop \"hotword → ask\" workflows"
msgstr "Flux de travail de bureau « mot-clé → demande »"

#: src/channels/voice.md:50
msgid "Always-listening home-automation agents"
msgstr "Agents d'automatisation domestique à écoute permanente"

#: src/channels/voice.md:52
msgid ""
"The agent doesn't send audio anywhere — wake detection is local. Only post-"
"wake speech goes through STT and reaches the LLM."
msgstr ""
"L'agent n'envoie l'audio nulle part — la détection de l'éveil est locale. "
"Seule la parole après l'éveil est traitée par la reconnaissance automatique "
"de la parole (STT) et atteint le modèle de langage (LLM)."

#: src/channels/voice.md:54
msgid "TTS (outbound speech synthesis)"
msgstr "TTS (synthèse vocale sortante)"

#: src/channels/voice.md:56
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.tts]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"engine = \"piper\"                   # local, free\n"
"voice = \"en_US-lessac-medium\"\n"
"output_device = \"default\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.tts]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"engine = \"piper\"                   # local, gratuit\n"
"voice = \"en_US-lessac-medium\"\n"
"output_device = \"default\"\n"
"```"

#: src/channels/voice.md:64
msgid "Other engines:"
msgstr "Autres moteurs :"

#: src/channels/voice.md:66
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.tts]\n"
"engine = \"openai\"                  # TTS-1 or TTS-1-HD\n"
"voice = \"alloy\"\n"
"api_key = \"...\"\n"
"\n"
"[channels.tts]\n"
"engine = \"elevenlabs\"\n"
"voice_id = \"21m00Tcm4TlvDq8ikWAM\"\n"
"api_key = \"...\"\n"
"\n"
"[channels.tts]\n"
"engine = \"google-cloud\"\n"
"voice = \"en-US-Neural2-J\"\n"
"credentials_json = \"~/.zeroclaw/gcp.json\"\n"
"\n"
"[channels.tts]\n"
"engine = \"edge\"                    # Microsoft Edge TTS — free, online\n"
"voice = \"en-US-AndrewNeural\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.tts]\n"
"engine = \"openai\"                  # TTS-1 ou TTS-1-HD\n"
"voice = \"alloy\"\n"
"api_key = \"...\"\n"
"\n"
"[channels.tts]\n"
"engine = \"elevenlabs\"\n"
"voice_id = \"21m00Tcm4TlvDq8ikWAM\"\n"
"api_key = \"...\"\n"
"\n"
"[channels.tts]\n"
"engine = \"google-cloud\"\n"
"voice = \"en-US-Neural2-J\"\n"
"credentials_json = \"~/.zeroclaw/gcp.json\"\n"
"\n"
"[channels.tts]\n"
"engine = \"edge\"                    # Microsoft Edge TTS — gratuit, en "
"ligne\n"
"voice = \"en-US-AndrewNeural\"\n"
"```"

#: src/channels/voice.md:87
msgid ""
"TTS is output-only — it's not a conversation channel; it's a speaker for "
"other channels' replies. Pair with `voice_wake` for a complete local voice "
"assistant."
msgstr ""
"TTS est en sortie uniquement — ce n'est pas un canal de conversation ; c'est "
"un haut-parleur pour les réponses des autres canaux. Associez-le à "
"`voice_wake` pour un assistant vocal local complet."

#: src/channels/voice.md:91
msgid "Latency budget"
msgstr "Budget de latence"

#: src/channels/voice.md:93
msgid "Speech feels real-time below ~500 ms end-to-end. Practical budgets:"
msgstr ""
"La parole semble en temps réel en dessous de ~500 ms de bout en bout. "
"Budgets pratiques :"

#: src/channels/voice.md:95 src/hardware/arduino-uno-q-setup.md:11
#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:34
