msgstr "100–300 ms de RTT"

#: src/channels/voice.md:103
msgid ""
"ClawdTalk shortcuts several of these by keeping the audio stream live; "
"regular `voice_call` incurs STT + LLM + TTS sequentially."
msgstr ""
"ClawdTalk simplifie plusieurs de ces étapes en maintenant le flux audio en "
"direct ; un appel vocal standard implique STT + LLM + TTS de manière "
"séquentielle."

#: src/channels/voice.md:105
msgid "STT options"
msgstr "Options de STT"

#: src/channels/voice.md:107
msgid "The runtime picks STT based on `stt_provider`:"
msgstr "Le runtime sélectionne STT en fonction de `stt_provider` :"

#: src/channels/voice.md:109
msgid "`whisper` — local whisper.cpp; CPU-only works but GPU helps"
msgstr ""
"`whisper` — whisper.cpp local ; le fonctionnement uniquement sur CPU est "
"possible, mais l'utilisation du GPU est recommandée"

#: src/channels/voice.md:110
msgid "`openai-whisper` — hosted Whisper API"
msgstr "`openai-whisper` — API Whisper hébergée"

#: src/channels/voice.md:111
msgid "`deepgram` — real-time streaming STT (fastest)"
msgstr "`deepgram` — STT en streaming en temps réel (le plus rapide)"

#: src/channels/voice.md:112
msgid "`google-cloud-stt`"
msgstr "`google-cloud-stt`"

#: src/channels/voice.md:113
msgid "`azure-stt`"
msgstr "`azure-stt`"

#: src/channels/voice.md:115
msgid "Set in the voice channel's config (`stt_provider = \"deepgram\"`)."
msgstr ""
"Défini dans la configuration du canal vocal (`stt_provider = \"deepgram\"`)."

#: src/channels/voice.md:117
msgid "Hardware notes"
msgstr "Notes matérielles"

#: src/channels/voice.md:119
msgid "For always-on voice on an SBC:"
msgstr "Pour la voix en continu sur un SBC :"

#: src/channels/voice.md:121
msgid ""
"USB mic: any UAC-compliant mic works. `arecord -l` to verify the OS sees it"
msgstr ""
"Microphone USB : tout microphone conforme à la norme UAC fonctionne. "
"Utilisez `arecord -l` pour vérifier que le système d'exploitation le détecte."

#: src/channels/voice.md:122
msgid ""
"Speaker: either USB audio out or the SBC's onboard jack; set `output_device` "
"to the ALSA name"
msgstr ""
"Haut-parleur : soit la sortie audio USB, soit la prise intégrée du SBC ; "
"définissez `output_device` sur le nom ALSA"

#: src/channels/voice.md:123
msgid ""
"Microphones with built-in AEC (acoustic echo cancellation) dramatically "
"improve wake reliability when the speaker is nearby"
msgstr ""
"Les microphones avec AEC (annulation d'écho acoustique) intégrée améliorent "
"considérablement la fiabilité de l'éveil lorsque le haut-parleur est à "
"proximité."

#: src/channels/voice.md:125
msgid ""
"See [Hardware → Android](../hardware/android-setup.md) for Android-specific "
"audio setup."
msgstr ""
"Voir [Matériel → Android](../hardware/android-setup.md) pour la "
"configuration audio spécifique à Android."

#: src/channels/webhook.md:3
msgid ""
"A generic inbound HTTP channel. Any service that can POST a JSON payload "
"(GitHub, Linear, Sentry, Zapier, cron-job.org, your own scripts) can hand "
"work to the agent via a webhook URL."
msgstr ""
"Un canal HTTP entrant générique. Tout service capable d’envoyer un payload "
"JSON (GitHub, Linear, Sentry, Zapier, cron-job.org, vos propres scripts) "
"peut transmettre des tâches à l’agent via une URL de webhook."

#: src/channels/webhook.md:5
msgid ""
"Webhooks live inside the gateway — if the gateway is running, webhooks are "
"reachable at `/webhook/<name>`."
msgstr ""
"Les webhooks sont intégrés au sein du gateway — si le gateway est en cours "
"d’exécution, les webhooks sont accessibles à l’adresse `/webhook/<name>`."

#: src/channels/webhook.md:9
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.webhooks.github-issues]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"secret = \"...\"                    # HMAC secret for signature "
"verification\n"
"dispatch_to = \"sop:triage-issue\"  # or a conversation ID, or a system "
"prompt\n"
"allow_list = [\"github.com\"]       # enforce source IP allowlist\n"
"\n"
"[channels.webhooks.grafana]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"secret = \"...\"\n"
"dispatch_to = \"cron:alert-handler\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.webhooks.github-issues]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"secret = \"...\"                    # Secret HMAC pour la vérification de "
"signature\n"
"dispatch_to = \"sop:triage-issue\"  # ou un ID de conversation, ou une "
"invite système\n"
"allow_list = [\"github.com\"]       # appliquer une liste blanche d'adresses "
"IP source\n"
"\n"
"[channels.webhooks.grafana]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"secret = \"...\"\n"
"dispatch_to = \"cron:alert-handler\"\n"
"```"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:22
msgid "The `dispatch_to` field points the inbound event at one of:"
msgstr "Le champ `dispatch_to` dirige l'événement entrant vers l'un des :"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:24
msgid ""
"`sop:<name>` — runs a Standard Operating Procedure with the payload as input"
msgstr ""
"`sop:<name>` — exécute une Procédure Opérationnelle Standard avec la charge "
"utile en entrée"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:25
msgid "`cron:<name>` — triggers a scheduled job off-schedule"
msgstr "`cron:<name>` — déclenche une tâche planifiée hors de son horaire"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:26
msgid ""
"`conversation:<id>` — appends to a named conversation (agent responds "
"normally)"
msgstr ""
"`conversation:<id>` — ajoute à une conversation nommée (l'agent répond "
"normalement)"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:27
msgid ""
"`system:<prompt>` — runs a one-shot agent call with the payload appended to "
"a system prompt"
msgstr ""
"`system:<prompt>` — exécute un appel d'agent en une seule fois avec le "
"contenu ajouté à un prompt système"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:31
msgid ""
"GitHub, Stripe, Slack, and most major sources sign webhooks with HMAC. Set "
"`secret` to the shared secret; the channel verifies `X-Hub-Signature-256` / "
"`X-Signature` / equivalent before dispatching."
msgstr ""
"GitHub, Stripe, Slack et la plupart des sources majeures signent les "
"webhooks avec HMAC. Définissez `secret` sur le secret partagé ; le canal "
"vérifie `X-Hub-Signature-256` / `X-Signature` / équivalent avant de "
"dispatcher."

#: src/channels/webhook.md:33
msgid ""
"Sources without signing (open webhooks) should at minimum set `allow_list` "
"to restrict by source IP. A webhook URL with no auth and no IP allowlist is "
"an open ingress — don't."
msgstr ""
"Les sources sans signature (webhooks ouverts) doivent au moins définir "
"`allow_list` pour restreindre par adresse IP source. Une URL de webhook sans "
"authentification et sans liste d'autorisation d'adresse IP constitue une "
"entrée ouverte — à éviter."

#: src/channels/webhook.md:35
msgid "Shape of what the agent sees"
msgstr "Forme de ce que l'agent voit"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:37
msgid ""
"By default the agent receives the raw JSON payload as a user message. For "
"structured sources, use `template`:"
msgstr ""
"Par défaut, l'agent reçoit le payload JSON brut en tant que message "
"utilisateur. Pour les sources structurées, utilisez `template` :"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:39
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.webhooks.sentry]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"secret = \"...\"\n"
"dispatch_to = \"sop:investigate-error\"\n"
"template = \"\"\"\n"
"New Sentry alert:\n"
"Level: {{ payload.level }}\n"
"Title: {{ payload.title }}\n"
"URL: {{ payload.web_url }}\n"
"\n"
"Stack:\n"
"{{ payload.exception.values[0].stacktrace }}\n"
"\"\"\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.webhooks.sentry]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"secret = \"...\"\n"
"dispatch_to = \"sop:investigate-error\"\n"
"template = \"\"\"\n"
"Nouvelle alerte Sentry :\n"
"Niveau : {{ payload.level }}\n"
"Titre : {{ payload.title }}\n"
"URL : {{ payload.web_url }}\n"
"\n"
"Pile d'appels :\n"
"{{ payload.exception.values[0].stacktrace }}\n"
"\"\"\"\n"
"```"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:55
msgid ""
"Templates use MiniJinja; `payload` is the full JSON body, plus `headers` and "
"`query` for URL params."
msgstr ""
"Les modèles utilisent MiniJinja ; `payload` correspond au corps JSON "
"complet, ainsi que `headers` et `query` pour les paramètres d'URL."

#: src/channels/webhook.md:57
msgid "Replies"
msgstr "Réponses"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:59
msgid ""
"Webhook channels default to one-shot: the agent handles the event, writes to "
"the receipts log, and returns 200. For webhook sources that wait for a reply "
"(interactive bots, slash commands), set `reply_mode`:"
msgstr ""
"Les canaux Webhook sont par défaut en mode « one-shot » : l’agent gère "
"l’événement, écrit dans le journal des accusés de réception et renvoie un "
"code 200. Pour les sources Webhook qui attendent une réponse (bots "
"interactifs, commandes slash), définissez `reply_mode` :"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:61
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.webhooks.slack-slash]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"secret = \"...\"\n"
"reply_mode = \"inline-json\"        # respond to POST with {\"text\": \"..."
"\"}\n"
"template = \"{{ payload.text }}\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.webhooks.slack-slash]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"secret = \"...\"\n"
"reply_mode = \"inline-json\"        # répondre à POST avec {\"text\": \"..."
"\"}\n"
"template = \"{{ payload.text }}\"\n"
"```"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:69
msgid ""
"Supported reply modes: `status-only` (default, 200 OK), `inline-json`, "
"`inline-text`."
msgstr ""
"Modes de réponse pris en charge : `status-only` (par défaut, 200 OK), "
"`inline-json`, `inline-text`."

#: src/channels/webhook.md:71
msgid "Public exposure"
msgstr "Exposition publique"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:73
msgid ""
"By default the gateway binds to localhost only. To expose webhooks publicly:"
msgstr ""
"Par défaut, le gateway se lie uniquement à localhost. Pour exposer les "
"webhooks publiquement :"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:75
msgid ""
"**Reverse proxy** — run nginx / Caddy / Traefik in front, terminate TLS, "
"proxy to localhost. See [Operations → Network deployment](../ops/network-"
"deployment.md)."
msgstr ""
"**Proxy inverse** — exécutez nginx / Caddy / Traefik en amont, terminez TLS, "
"puis proxifiez vers localhost. Consultez [Opérations → Déploiement réseau]"
"(../ops/network-deployment.md)."

#: src/channels/webhook.md:76
msgid ""
"**Tunnel** — configure `[tunnel] provider = \"ngrok\" | \"cloudflare\" | "
"\"tailscale\"` and restart the daemon. Tunnels start alongside the gateway."
msgstr ""
"**Tunnel** — configurez `[tunnel] provider = \"ngrok\" | \"cloudflare\" | "
"\"tailscale\"` et redémarrez le daemon. Les tunnels démarrent en même temps "
"que la passerelle."

