#: src/ops/network-deployment.md:18
msgid ""
"**Upshot:** a Telegram-only bot runs on a Pi behind a consumer router with "
"zero port forwarding. Anything webhook-based needs a reachable URL — which "
"is where tunnels come in."
msgstr ""
"**Conclusion :** un bot Telegram-only s'exécute sur un Pi derrière un "
"routeur grand public sans aucune redirection de port. Tout ce qui est basé "
"sur les webhooks nécessite une URL accessible — c'est là que les tunnels "
"entrent en jeu."

#: src/ops/network-deployment.md:20
msgid "Binding the gateway"
msgstr "Liaison de la passerelle"

#: src/ops/network-deployment.md:22
msgid ""
"By default the gateway binds to `127.0.0.1` — unreachable from other "
"devices. Three options to expose it:"
msgstr ""
"Par défaut, la passerelle se lie à `127.0.0.1` — inaccessible depuis "
"d'autres appareils. Trois options pour l'exposer :"

#: src/ops/network-deployment.md:24
msgid "Option 1 — Public bind (LAN)"
msgstr "Option 1 — Liaison publique (LAN)"

#: src/ops/network-deployment.md:26
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[gateway]\n"
"host = \"0.0.0.0\"\n"
"port = 42617\n"
"allow_public_bind = true     # required safety flag\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[gateway]\n"
"host = \"0.0.0.0\"\n"
"port = 42617\n"
"allow_public_bind = true     # indicateur de sécurité requis\n"
"```"

#: src/ops/network-deployment.md:33
msgid ""
"Then any device on the LAN can reach `http://<pi-ip>:42617`. Doesn't help "
"for internet-reachable webhooks — your router's public IP isn't forwarded to "
"the Pi."
msgstr ""
"Ensuite, n'importe quel appareil sur le LAN peut accéder à `http://<pi-"
"ip>:42617`. Cela ne convient pas pour les webhooks accessibles depuis "
"Internet — l'adresse IP publique de votre routeur n'est pas redirigée vers "
"le Pi."

#: src/ops/network-deployment.md:35
msgid ""
"**Safety:** `allow_public_bind = true` is required because binding to "
"`0.0.0.0` is a significant posture change. Without it, the daemon refuses. "
"This is deliberate."
msgstr ""
"**Sécurité :** `allow_public_bind = true` est requis car la liaison à "
"`0.0.0.0` constitue un changement significatif de posture. Sans cette "
"option, le daemon refuse. C'est intentionnel."

#: src/ops/network-deployment.md:37
msgid "Option 2 — Tunnel (internet-reachable)"
msgstr "Option 2 — Tunnel (accessible depuis Internet)"

#: src/ops/network-deployment.md:39
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[tunnel]\n"
"provider = \"tailscale\"       # or \"cloudflare\", \"ngrok\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[tunnel]\n"
"provider = \"tailscale\"       # ou \"cloudflare\", \"ngrok\"\n"
"```"

#: src/ops/network-deployment.md:44
msgid ""
"Then restart the daemon — the tunnel is managed declaratively from config, "
"starting alongside the gateway."
msgstr ""
"Redémarrez ensuite le daemon — le tunnel est géré de manière déclarative "
"depuis la configuration, en démarrant en même temps que la passerelle."

#: src/ops/network-deployment.md:46
msgid ""
"The tunnel forwards from a public URL to the gateway on `127.0.0.1`. No "
"router config, no opened ports. All three supported tunnels work similarly:"
msgstr ""
"Le tunnel redirige une URL publique vers la passerelle sur `127.0.0.1`. "
"Aucune configuration de routeur, aucun port ouvert. Les trois types de "
"tunnels pris en charge fonctionnent de manière similaire :"

