#: src/sop/syntax.md:1
msgid "SOP Syntax Reference"
msgstr "Référence de la syntaxe SOP"

#: src/sop/syntax.md:3
msgid ""
"SOP definitions are loaded from subdirectories under `sops_dir` (default: "
"`<workspace>/sops`)."
msgstr ""
"Les définitions de SOP sont chargées à partir des sous-répertoires sous "
"`sops_dir` (par défaut : `<workspace>/sops`)."

#: src/sop/syntax.md:5
msgid "1. Directory Layout"
msgstr "1. Structure des répertoires"

#: src/sop/syntax.md:14
msgid ""
"Each SOP must have `SOP.toml`. `SOP.md` is optional, but runs with no parsed "
"steps will fail validation."
msgstr ""
"Chaque SOP doit avoir `SOP.toml`. `SOP.md` est optionnel, mais échouera à la "
"validation s'il n'exécute aucune étape analysée."

#: src/sop/syntax.md:16
msgid "2. `SOP.toml`"
msgstr "2. `SOP.toml`"

#: src/sop/syntax.md:18
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[sop]\n"
"name = \"deploy-prod\"\n"
"description = \"Deploy service to production\"\n"
"version = \"1.0.0\"\n"
"priority = \"high\"              # low | normal | high | critical\n"
"execution_mode = \"supervised\"  # auto | supervised | step_by_step | "
"priority_based\n"
"cooldown_secs = 300\n"
"max_concurrent = 1\n"
"\n"
"[[triggers]]\n"
"type = \"webhook\"\n"
"path = \"/sop/deploy\"\n"
"\n"
"[[triggers]]\n"
"type = \"manual\"\n"
"\n"
"[[triggers]]\n"
"type = \"mqtt\"\n"
"topic = \"ops/deploy\"\n"
"condition = \"$.env == \\\"prod\\\"\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[sop]\n"
"name = \"deploy-prod\"\n"
"description = \"Déployer le service en production\"\n"
"version = \"1.0.0\"\n"
"priority = \"high\"              # low | normal | high | critical\n"
"execution_mode = \"supervised\"  # auto | supervised | step_by_step | "
"priority_based\n"
"cooldown_secs = 300\n"
"max_concurrent = 1\n"
"\n"
"[[triggers]]\n"
"type = \"webhook\"\n"
"path = \"/sop/deploy\"\n"
"\n"
"[[triggers]]\n"
"type = \"manual\"\n"
"\n"
"[[triggers]]\n"
"type = \"mqtt\"\n"
"topic = \"ops/deploy\"\n"
"condition = \"$.env == \\\"prod\\\"\"\n"
"```"

#: src/sop/syntax.md:41
msgid "3. `SOP.md` Step Format"
msgstr "3. Format des étapes de `SOP.md`"

#: src/sop/syntax.md:43
msgid "Steps are parsed from the `## Steps` section."
msgstr "Les étapes sont analysées à partir de la section `## Steps`."

#: src/sop/syntax.md:56
msgid "Parser behavior:"
msgstr "Comportement de l'analyseur :"

#: src/sop/syntax.md:58
msgid "Numbered items (`1.`, `2.`, ...) define step order."
msgstr ""
"Les éléments numérotés (`1.`, `2.`, ...) définissent l'ordre des étapes."

#: src/sop/syntax.md:59
msgid "Leading bold text (`**Title**`) becomes step title."
msgstr "Le texte en gras (`**Titre**`) devient le titre de l'étape."

#: src/sop/syntax.md:60
msgid "`- tools:` maps to `suggested_tools`."
msgstr "`- tools:` est mappé vers `suggested_tools`."

#: src/sop/syntax.md:61
msgid "`- requires_confirmation: true` enforces approval for that step."
msgstr ""
"`- requires_confirmation: true` impose une approbation pour cette étape."

#: src/sop/syntax.md:63
msgid "4. Trigger Types"
msgstr "4. Types de déclencheurs"

#: src/sop/syntax.md:65
msgid "Fields"
msgstr "Champs"

#: src/sop/syntax.md:67
msgid "`manual`"
msgstr "`manuel`"

#: src/sop/syntax.md:67
msgid "none"
msgstr "aucun"

#: src/sop/syntax.md:67
msgid "Triggered by tool `sop_execute` (not a `zeroclaw sop run` CLI command)."
msgstr ""
"Déclenché par l'outil `sop_execute` (et non par la commande CLI `zeroclaw "
"sop run`)."

#: src/sop/syntax.md:68
msgid "`path`"
msgstr "`chemin`"

#: src/sop/syntax.md:68
msgid "Exact match against request path (`/sop/...` or `/webhook`)."
msgstr ""
"Correspondance exacte avec le chemin de la requête (`/sop/...` ou `/"
"webhook`)."

#: src/sop/syntax.md:69
msgid "`topic`, optional `condition`"
msgstr "`topic`, `condition` optionnel"

#: src/sop/syntax.md:69
msgid "MQTT topic supports `+` and `#` wildcards."
msgstr "Le sujet MQTT prend en charge les jokers `+` et `#`."

#: src/sop/syntax.md:70
msgid "`expression`"
msgstr "`expression`"

#: src/sop/syntax.md:70
msgid "Supports 5, 6, or 7 fields (5-field gets seconds prepended internally)."
msgstr ""
"Prend en charge 5, 6 ou 7 champs (le champ de 5 champs ajoute des secondes "
"en interne)."

#: src/sop/syntax.md:71
msgid "`peripheral`"
msgstr "`périphérique`"

#: src/sop/syntax.md:71
msgid "`board`, `signal`, optional `condition`"
msgstr "`board`, `signal`, condition optionnelle"

#: src/sop/syntax.md:71
msgid "Matches `\"{board}/{signal}\"`."
msgstr "Correspond à `\"{board}/{signal}\"`."

#: src/sop/syntax.md:73
msgid "5. Condition Syntax"
msgstr "5. Syntaxe des conditions"

#: src/sop/syntax.md:75
msgid ""
"`condition` is evaluated fail-closed (invalid condition/payload => no match)."
msgstr ""
"`condition` est évalué en mode « échec fermé » (condition/payload invalide "
"=> aucune correspondance)."

#: src/sop/syntax.md:77
msgid "JSON path comparisons: `$.value > 85`, `$.status == \"critical\"`"
msgstr ""
"Comparaisons de chemins JSON : `$.value > 85`, `$.status == \"critical\"`"

#: src/sop/syntax.md:78
msgid "Direct numeric comparisons: `> 0` (useful for simple payloads)"
msgstr ""
"Comparaisons numériques directes : `> 0` (utile pour les payloads simples)"

#: src/sop/syntax.md:79
msgid "Operators: `>=`, `<=`, `!=`, `>`, `<`, `==`"
msgstr "Opérateurs : `>=`, `<=`, `!=`, `>`, `<`, `==`"

#: src/sop/syntax.md:81
msgid "6. Validation"
msgstr "6. Validation"

#: src/sop/syntax.md:83 src/sop/connectivity.md:65
msgid "Use:"
msgstr "Utiliser :"

#: src/sop/syntax.md:90
msgid ""
"Validation warns on empty names/descriptions, missing triggers, missing "
"steps, and step numbering gaps."
msgstr ""
"La validation émet des avertissements en cas de noms/descriptions vides, de "
"déclencheurs manquants, d'étapes manquantes et de lacunes dans la "
"numérotation des étapes."

